edu.nyu.cs.addressbook

Class ContactEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.nyu.cs.addressbook.ContactEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<ContactEntry>

    public class ContactEntry
extends Object
implements Comparable<ContactEntry>
    Author:
    shenli

    The ContactEntry class represents contact entry information.

    ContactEntry objects are not constant; their values could be changed after they are created. The ContactEntry object is not thread-safe. To use it concurrently, user must surround each method invocation with external synchronization of the users' choosing.

        public List<PhoneNumber> getPhoneNumbers()
        Returns an unmodifiable view of the phone number list. This method allows modules to provide users with "read-only" access to internal lists. Query operations on the returned list "read through" to the specified list, and attempts to modify the returned list, whether direct or via its iterator, result in an UnsupportedOperationException.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this ContactEntry for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a ContactEntry object, both objects have the same last name and first name.

        This implementation first checks if the specified object is this ContactEntry. If so, it returns true; if not, it checks if the specified object is a ContactEntry object. If not, it returns false; if so, it iterates over both ContactEntry objects, comparing corresponding fields. If any comparison returns false, this method returns false. Otherwise it returns true when the iterations complete.

        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Parameters:

        public String toString()
        Returns string representation of this ContactEntry object. The string format is as "firstname lastname\nphone number ...\nemail address ...\npostal address ...\nnote". Note that there is a single space separating the first name and last name.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(ContactEntry ce)
        Compares the contact entries represented by two ContactEntry objects. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified object.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable<ContactEntry>
        Parameters:
        ce - the ContactEntry to be compared.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if the contact entry represented by the argument is equal to the contact entry represented by this ContactEntry; a value less than 0 if the contact entry of this ContactEntry is lexicographically less than the contact entry represented by the argument; and a value greater than 0 if the contact entry of this ContactEntry is lexicographically greater than the contact entry represented by the argument.
